= Group 17
== Physical properties of the Group 17 elements
The Group 17 elements are called the _halogens_.
#point[Describe the colours and the trend in volatility of chlorine, bromine and iodine]
The _volatility_ of a substance is the ease with which it eveaporates.
- Fluorine is a pale yellow gas
- Chlorine is a pale yellow-green gas
- Bromine is an orange-brown liquid
- Iodine is a grey-black solid
_Volatility decreases down the group._ This is because evaporation requires the breaking of
intermolecular forces. In halogens, the intermolecular forces are in the form of 
id--id#footnote[instantaneous dipole--induced dipole] forces, and down the group, the number
of electrons per molecule increases. Thus, down the group, intermolecular forces increase,
and hence volatility decreases.

#point[Describe and explain the trend in the bond strength of the halogen molecules]
_The halogens get less reactive going down Group 17._ This is because the electronegativity of the
halogen molecule  decreases down the group, which is because of the trend in atomic radii of the
elements in the group. In the example of fluorine, its outer shell is nearest to the
attractive force of the nucleus and an electron entering its outer shell will  also experience
the least shielding from the attraction of the positive nuclear charge. _Greater shielding
outweighs the attraction to electrons from the significantly greater nuclear charge down the 
group, hence, bond strength decreases down the group._

